Citroën’s return to South Africa earlier this year after a three year hiatus has been an eagerly awaited one with a three model line-up packed to the brim with features and styled in a typical quirky way only the marque can pull-off. As a means of catering to all, Andre de Kock went on a mud plugging track behind the wheel of the high-riding C3 Aircross, while Charl Bosch took command of the model on which it is based, the standard C3. C3 Aircross This writer recently had a sophisticated French model as a house guest for a full week....